FATHER STANLEY FLETCHER is a Forest Ranger. He knows everything there is to know about living in the great outdoors and loves to share his knowledge with the boys and girls of Sylvania. Whatever Stanley has planned, you can be sure he always rounds everyone up at the end of each day and leads them safely back home!

entry.title: Baerenwald Forest Families Parrot Family of 4 - RARE VINTAGE
entry.summary:
Vendor: Sylvanian Families pre-owned
Type: Sylvanian Families

Baerenwald Forest Families Parrot Family of 4 - RARE VINTAGE

This gorgeous Parrot family is not Sylvanian, but is in fact a vintage Forest Families Brand set from the 1980's.  There were several different brands on the market in the 1980's/early 1990's selling similar flocked figures to the Sylvanian range. 

Points to Note

- Glue marking -  Mr Parrot has some flocking defects on his head (where his hat originally had been glued on) See images below. Mr Parrot also has a tiny knick on his flocking on the base of his tail. 

- Clothing - Originally Mrs Parrot wore a blue dress, but this unfortunately isn't with the set. Also Mr Parrot wore a black hat, which in the original set would have been glued to his head (this is how they were sold) however, unfortunately his hat has been removed by a previous owner, leaving a glue mark and defect on his flocking.

- Mrs Parrot has a small red mark beside her nose. See close up pictures. 

Sizing: The below picture shows Freya Rabbit alongside the Parrot Family. Freya the Sylvanian Rabbit is not included, but is only in images to show the height of the figures in comparison to a Sylvanian figure.

 

Overall, in spite of the points mentioned above, these are in beautiful, bright and gorgeous condition. They are a rarity and a prize for any collection.

Condition: Very Good pre-owned vintage condition. 

This sale is for 4 x pre-owned Forest Families vintage figures.

No box

entry.title: Sylvanian Families Dandelion/Ivory Twin Rabbits - RARE
entry.summary:
Vendor: Sylvanian Families pre-owned
Type: Toy
Price: 45.00

Sylvanian Families Dandelion Twin Rabbits of also known as Ivory Rabbits or also Butterglove rabbits - Preowned - RARE1992

The family name of these twins is all a little bit confusing. Their family members, over time, have been known by various names: Ivory Rabbits, Butterglove Rabbits and these twins, when they were released, were called Dandelion Rabbit Twins. 

Ivory Rabbits were released exclusively in Japan in the late 1990's. Later the Butterglove Rabbits were released, not as a family, but in individual sets with accessories in the UK around 2001 and onward.

The Dandelion rabbit twins are known by one distinctively floppy ear, one ear bent more than the other. They're more of a fawn brown colour than the milk rabbits and yet not as dark as a Dappledawn rabbit. 

Excellent condition. Only a tiny little bit of wear on the tip of one's ears.  Brother twin's romper pants are a little twisted.

Very collectible. Hard to find

No box

As we mention with all of our pre-owned items, they will never be as immaculate as a brand new item. There may be slight signs of playwear or use in any pre-owned figure. Also limbs may be slightly stiff to move, due to age.
